DataElement.preferredDefinition: A mark on a substance or body made by foreign matter; a blot; a place discolored.:A usually 2-dimensional diagrammatic representation of an object or area._Chemical substances that are used to stain and color other materials. The coloring may or may not be permanent. Dyes can also be used as therapeutic agents and test reagents in medicine and scientific research.:A substance that is identifiable by virtue of its radioactive signature, color, or other distinguishing physical property, such as a dye, radioactive isotope, or inert chemical, that is introduced into a biological or mechanical system and can be followed through the course of a process, providing information on the pattern of events in the process or on the redistribution of the parts, elements, or events involved._Generic value domain for a java datatype that is a class that represents character strings.

Concepts.definition: Agents used to enhance the color or contrast of target materials or samples. Dyes have some affinity for their substrates and are usually applied in a solution.

A substance that is identifiable by virtue of its radioactive signature, color, or other distinguishing physical property, such as a dye, radioactive isotope, or inert chemical, that is introduced into a biological or mechanical system and can be followed through the course of a process, providing information on the pattern of events in the process or on the redistribution of the parts, elements, or events involved.
